			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To all the previous postings that focus on druids using scimitars.... Druids have always been able to use scimitars.  Yes it is true that they prefer only &quot;natural&quot; weapons and simple weapons. The reason why they are able to use a scimitar is becuase of their religious belief in the sun and the moon. The scimitar is a curved weapon which resembles the cresent shape of the moon or the sun. They are also known to use a sickle or a scythe for the same reasons. The use of all other weapons are restricted to thier belief of using natural weapons and for the flat reason that they are priests and devote much of their time to study and prayer, not combat. Hope this helps, Fenderous Wind'Chaser
				</font>
